Explain casting, up-casting, down-casting.

Up-casting is when an object is in a group and the object acts
as if it is on its own.
Down-casting is when an object can manipulate its self over 
and over again.

Ex of up-casting:
int bubbles = 10;
double foam;
foam = bubbles;

How to change a string to a char.
char hi = 'I';
string hello;
hello = "" + hi;
